Usage: voltdb start [ OPTIONS ... ]

Starts a database, which has been initialized.

Options:
  --version             show program's version number and exit
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -v, --verbose         display verbose messages and external commands
  --admin=ADMINPORT     specify the admin port as [ipaddress:]port-number
  --client=CLIENTPORT   specify the client port as [ipaddress:]port-number
  --drpublic=DRPUBLIC   Specifies the interface (ipaddress[:port-number])
                        advertised to consumer clusters as the DR interface,
                        used in hosted environments where internal interfaces
                        are not reachable
  --externalinterface=EXTERNALINTERFACE
                        specify the network interface to use for external
                        ports, such as the admin and client ports
  --http=HTTPPORT       specify the http port as [ipaddress:]port-number
  --ignore=SKIP_REQUIREMENTS
                        requirements to skip when start voltdb:
                        thp - Checking for Transparent Huge Pages (THP) has
                        been disabled.  Use of THP can cause VoltDB to run out
                        of memory. Do not disable this check on production
                        systems. (default=None)
  --internal=INTERNALPORT
                        specify the internal port as [ipaddress:]port-number
                        used to communicate between cluster nodes
  --internalinterface=INTERNALINTERFACE
                        specify the network interface to use for internal
                        communication, such as the internal and zookeeper
                        ports
  --publicinterface=PUBLICINTERFACE
                        For hosted or cloud environments with non-public
                        interfaces, this argument specifies a publicly-
                        accessible alias for reaching the server. Particularly
                        useful for remote access to the VoltDB Management
                        Center.
  --replication=REPLICATIONPORT
                        specify the replication port as [ipaddress:]port-
                        number (1st of 3 sequential ports)
  --topicsport=TOPICSPORT
                        specify the topics port as [ipaddress:]port-number
  --zookeeper=ZKPORT    specify the zookeeper port as [ipaddress:]port-number
  -A, --add             allows the server to elastically expand the cluster if
                        the cluster is already complete (default=False)
  -B, --background      run the VoltDB server in the background (as a daemon
                        process)
  -c HOSTCOUNT, --count=HOSTCOUNT
                        number of hosts in the cluster
  -D DIRECTORY_SPEC, --dir=DIRECTORY_SPEC
                        Specifies the root directory for the database. The
                        default is voltdbroot under the current working
                        directory. (default=None)
  -g PLACEMENTGROUP, --placement-group=PLACEMENTGROUP
                        placement group (default="0")
  -H SERVER_LIST, --host=SERVER_LIST
                        {hostname-or-ip[,...]}, Specifies the leader(s) for
                        coordinating cluster startup.  (default="")
  -l LICENSE, --license=LICENSE
                        specify the location of the license file
  -m MISSING, --missing=MISSING
                        specifying how many nodes are missing at K-safe
                        cluster startup
  -p, --pause           Start Database in paused mode.
  -r, --replica         start replica cluster (deprecated, please use
                        role="replica" in the deployment file) (default=False)


